The paper deals with learning evolving entity representations over time in dynamic knowledge graphs, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses modeling the occurrence of a fact as a point process, which is a common technique in the field of databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions predicting the occurrence or recurrence time of a fact, which is a task related to temporal reasoning and could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or natural language processing (cs.CL).
